Los_Angeles.City House and the Olympic: City House and The Olympic is a cancelled residential skyscraper complex proposed for the southeast corner of South Grand Avenue and West Olympic Boulevard in Los Angeles, California. It was designed by Robertson Partners, and developed by The Titan Organization. City House would have had 60 floors and been 229 m (751 ft) in height, and the Olympic would have had 50 floors and been 173 m (568 ft) tall.
